&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Maintain accurate and up-to-date banking records&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Complete bank reconciliations in Xero&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&q

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Associate Paraplanner supports the advice team by preparing advice documentation, conducting research and assisting with the administration and implementation of financial advice strategies. This role is designed as a development opportunity for individuals seeking to build strong technical foundations and progress towards a long-term career in financial planning. Working alongside experienced Advisers and Paraplanners, the Associate Paraplanner will develop advice preparation skills, technical knowledge and an understanding of the end-to-end advice process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the preparation of Statements of Advice (SoAs), Records of Advice (RoAs), Review Reports and other advice documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather, collate and validate client information required for advice preparation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate client records and data within Xplan and other business systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with research on investments, superannuation, insurance and other financial products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the preparation of cashflow projections, modelling and strategy analysis under the guidance of Advisers and Paraplanners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the preparation of portfolio reviews, investment reports and client presentation materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support implementation activities and follow-up requests with product providers, insurers and external stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor workflows and assist with the timely completion of advice-related tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure documentation and file management practices comply with organizational and regulatory requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with maintaining advice templates and supporting advice production processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop an understanding of wholesale and retail investment products through hands-on experience and training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Advisers, CSOs and Paraplanners to support client outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in training, professional development and mentoring opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to continuous improvement initiatives within the advice support team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1–2 years&#39; experience in financial services, client service, administration or adviser support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RG146 compliant or willingness to obtain.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree in Finance, Economics, Commerce or Business desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Genuine interest in pursuing a long-term career in financial planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to Xplan or similar financial planning software desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills and Attributes:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational and administrative skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High attention to detail and accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Desire to learn and develop technical financial planning knowledge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in investments, superannuation, retirement planning and personal insurance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving capability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage competing priorities and meet deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative approach and willingness to seek feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Positive attitude and commitment to professional development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
