&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Managing job workflows in practice management systems&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Monitoring deadlines and bottlenecks and raising these to support an exceptional client experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;The purpose of the Client Service Manager (CSM) is to proactively assist the Financial Adviser/s to exceed their clients’ expectations and financial planning requirements by assuming responsibility for the day-to-day administration and implementation activities. On behalf of Focus Partners Australia Wealth and the Financial Adviser’s proactively and professionally liaise with and provide support to clients, to exceed their expectations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;This role is located in Brisbane, Queensland, Australia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;First point of contact with client and triaging client calls and emails for advisers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Prepare for client meetings and proactively support the Client Services team by effectively and efficiently managing assigned duties.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Coordinate client meeting bookings for the Financial Adviser(s) and manage all meeting requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Prepare the required documentation for meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Identify and advise the client of any information/documentation required to have available for the meeting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Attend client meetings and take appropriate meeting notes – as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Record actions and tasks in Financial Planning administration system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Take ownership and proactively manage assigned responsibilities on behalf of the Financial Adviser/s.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Liaise with external parties (product providers and the clients other professional advisers) to collect client information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Proactively support Financial Adviser (s)by effectively and efficiently managing the assigned tasks as required by the Financial Adviser(s).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Coordinate and liaise between clients, Adviser/s, Accountants (internal &amp;amp; external) and other teams/external organisations e.g. ATO, Centrelink, fund managers and superannuation companies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Liaise with clients to keep them informed of the status of the strategy recommendations implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Agree on approach with the Financial Adviser(s) relating to management of client reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Complete and send out Annual Engagements and Fee Consent forms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Complete required documentation to support the review process including but not limited to: Fact Find.
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Current Financial Plan.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Financial Planning software reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Other documents may apply to specific processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Attend relevant courses and actively take part in training or other activities to stay current with financial planning administration, client service and implementation practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Qualif

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Client Service Officer (CSO) plays a key role in supporting Financial Advisers and delivering an exceptional client experience. The role is responsible for managing client administration, coordinating the implementation of advice recommendations, and providing ongoing service and support to clients throughout their advice journey. Working closely with advisers, clients and external stakeholders, the CSO ensures client requests and advice implementation activities are managed efficiently, accurately and in line with compliance requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively support Financial Advisers by managing assigned tasks, priorities and administrative responsibilities to ensure efficient delivery of client outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow up clients on outstanding items such as Authority to Proceed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and advise clients of any information or documentation required for meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and liaise with clients, Financial Advisers, product providers, accountants, professional advisers and external organizations to obtain information and support the implementation of client strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with clients to keep them informed of the progress of advice implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage advice implementation workflows and follow up platform, superannuation, insurance and investment providers to ensure recommendations are completed accurately and within required timeframes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to general client enquiries that do not require financial advice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate client records, actions, workflows and compliance documentation within Xplan and other business systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend relevant training and professional development activities to maintain current knowledge of financial planning administration, client service and implementation practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide reception support and assist with incoming calls during peak periods and team absences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 to 5 years&#39; experience in a Client Service Officer or similar role within financial planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting the implementation of financial advice recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience administering superannuation, investment and insurance products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with financial planning software such as Xplan.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using major investment and superannuation platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of ASIC compliance and financial advice administration requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience within a financial planning practice is highly regarded.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills and Attributes:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple workflows and meet deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Microsoft Excel, Word, Outlook and Adobe Acrobat Pro.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High attention to detail and accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to remain calm and organized when working under pressure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fast learner with strong adaptability and willingness to embrace change.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational and time management skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work autonomously while contributing effectively as part of a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong client service focus with a commitment to delivering a high-quality client experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
